 ','line_number':1,'multiline':True]['text':' Verify that in progress index builds report matching 'spec' and 'building: true' in the output of','line_number':34,'multiline':False]['text':' $indexStats.','line_number':35,'multiline':False]['text':' Enable 'hangAfterStartingIndexBuild' failpoint on each of the primaries. This will make index','line_number':37,'multiline':False]['text':' building process infinite.','line_number':38,'multiline':False]['text':' Wait for the failpoint to be hit on each of the primaries.','line_number':51,'multiline':False]['text':' This ensures that the index build started. We cannot use','line_number':52,'multiline':False]['text':' 'IndexBuildTest.waitForIndexBuildToStart()' for it because it checks if any index build operation','line_number':53,'multiline':False]['text':' exists. In the sharded cluster it may lead to the situation where only one shard has started','line_number':54,'multiline':False]['text':' index build and triggered 'waitForIndexBuildToStart' to return. We want to wait for all shards','line_number':55,'multiline':False]['text':' to start index building before proceeding with the test.','line_number':56,'multiline':False]['text':' This also ensures that the index was added to the catalog, so that in can be seen by $indexStats','line_number':57,'multiline':False]['text':' stage (see SERVER-54172 for details).','line_number':58,'multiline':False]['text':' Each index should report building: true since the index build was paused.','line_number':72,'multiline':False]['text':' Each index should report a spec that matches the parameters passed to createIndex().','line_number':74,'multiline':False]['text':' In the sharded case, record the reported shard names and compare them against the','line_number':80,'multiline':False]['text':' names of known shards.','line_number':81,'multiline':False]['text':' Turn off failpoint on each of the primaries','line_number':93,'multiline':False]['text':' Wait until all index building operations stop. It is safe to use','line_number':96,'multiline':False]['text':' 'IndexBuildTest.waitForIndexBuildToStop()' here because it ensures that no index building','line_number':97,'multiline':False]['text':' operation exists. So in the sharded cluster, this function will return only when all shards','line_number':98,'multiline':False]['text':' stopped index building.','line_number':99,'multiline':False]['text':' Verify that there is no 'building' field in the $indexStats output for our created index once the','line_number':104,'multiline':False]['text':' index build is complete.','line_number':105,'multiline':False]